{{italic title}} '''''Boomerang!''''' is a monthly audio magazine for children.<ref>{{cite news|author=Laurel Shaper Walters|title=Cousins to Books on Tape, 'Audiomagazines' Engage Children|url=http://www.csmonitor.com/1996/0304/04132.html|accessdate=31 October 2015|work=The Christian Science Monitor|date=4 March 1996|location=St. Louis}}</ref><ref name=din>{{cite web|title=Resource: Boomerang! The Audio Magazine|url=http://www.davidsongifted.org/db/Resources_id_11600.aspx|publisher=Davidson Institute|accessdate=31 October 2015}}</ref> The magazine is based in [[San Francisco, California]].<ref name="ianf"/>
==History ad profile== ''Boomerang!'' was founded by [[David Strohm]] in San Francisco in 1990.<ref name="ianf">{{cite news|author=Ian Fischer|title=A Magazine to Please Children's Ears|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1991/11/03/education/blackboard-a-magazine-to-please-children-s-ears.html|accessdate=13 February 2016|work=The New York Times|date=3 November 1991}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Guy|url=http://www.davidstrohm.com/new-page/|work=David Strohm website|accessdate=13 February 2016}}</ref> He continues to head-up the audio magazine's content development and day-to-day operations.<ref>{{cite web|author=Michael Leppert|title=Boomerang! The Kids' Audio Magazine|url=http://www.homeschoolnewslink.com/homeschool/productguide/boomerang.shtml|work=Arts Instruction Schools|accessdate=31 October 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160216215900/http://www.homeschoolnewslink.com/homeschool/productguide/boomerang.shtml|archivedate=16 February 2016|df=}}</ref> The magazine targets children aged 6-12.<ref name=din/> It was an advertisement-free magazine during the 1990s.<ref name="ianf"/>
==Awards== ''Boomerang!'' received the [[American Library Association]]'s [[Notable Recording Award]], the [[Parent's Choice Award]] and the Educational Press Association Award for excellence in news reporting and was included in [[Dr. Toy]]'s 100 Best Children's Products.<ref>{{cite web|title=Boomerang! Audio for Kids|url=http://homeedmag.com/resources/curriculum/curriculum-programs/boomerang-audio-for-kids/|work=Homeschooling Resources|accessdate=31 October 2015|date=10 December 2010}}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
