{{Orphan|date=August 2010}} {{Infobox person | name = Ismail Mahmoud al-Qabbani | image = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1898 | birth_place = [[Asyut Governorate]], Egypt | death_date = 1963 | death_place = | nationality = Egyptian | other_names = | known_for = Educational reform | occupation = Minister of Education }} '''Ismail al-Qabbani''' ({{lang-ar|إسماعيل القباني}}; born in 1898 in [[Asyut Governorate]]–1963) was an [[Egypt]]ian reforming educationalist. He introduced to the [[Education in Egypt|Egyptian education system]] the concept of [[Pragmatism]]. He was also convinced that education in Egypt should be indigenous and rooted in [[Egyptian culture|Egyptian]] and [[Arabic culture]].<ref name=ttrb1>{{cite web|url=http://www.ttrb.ac.uk/viewArticle2.aspx?contentId=13152 |title=Ismail al-Qabbani: Educational Thinker |publisher=Ttrb.ac.uk |date=2007-02-18 |accessdate=2011-03-02}}</ref> He became Dean of the Institute of Education. He established the ''Journal of Modern Education''<ref>[http://www.ibe.unesco.org/publications/ThinkersPdf/qabbanie.pdf Ismai'il al-Qabbani in Prospects : the quarterly review of comparative education, Paris, UNESCO : International Bureau of Education, vol. XXIV, no. 1/2, 1994, p. 355-374]</ref> in 1948 and later became [[Ministry of Education (Egypt)|Minister for Education]].
