{{Infobox book | name = Wonders of the Solar System | image = Wonders of the Solar System (book).jpg| caption = | author = [[Brian Cox (physicist)|Brian Cox]], Andrew Cohen | language = English | genre = [[Non-fiction]] | subject = [[Physics]], [[cosmology]], [[universe]] | country = | publisher = Collins | pub_date = 2010 | pages = 256 pp. | isbn = 9780007386901 | preceded_by = [[Why Does E=mc2?]] | followed_by = [[Wonders of the Universe (book)|Wonders of the Universe]] }} '''''Wonders of the Solar System''''' is a 2010 book by the [[Theoretical physics|theoretical physicists]] [[Brian Cox (physicist)|Brian Cox]] and Andrew Cohen. The book is about [[Universe|the universe]], [[cosmology]] as well as [[Solar System|the Solar System]], and is explained in a way that is accessible to a general reader. The book is based on a series with the same name [[Wonders of the Solar System (TV series)|Wonders of the Solar System]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Wonders of the Solar System and A Kick in the Head {{!}} TV Review|url = https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2010/mar/08/wonders-of-the-solar-system|website = the Guardian|accessdate = 2015-11-21|first = Sam|last = Wollaston}}</ref>
